  "footnotes": [
    "Duchy of Carantania: The earliest known Slavic principality (c.630s); its Christianisation (c.745) and ritual ducal investiture ceremony ('Knežji kamen') were unique in medieval Europe.",
    "French Illyrian Provinces (1809–13): Napoleonic administration centred on Ljubljana; introduced French legal codes and promoted Slovenian language in administration.",
    "Istrian Zone B: After WWII Istria was split into Italian Zone A (Trieste) and Yugoslav Zone B (Koper/Capodistria area); Zone B became Slovenian in 1954, confirmed by Treaty of Osimo (1975).",
    "Ten-Day War (1991): Slovenia's brief independence war against the Yugoslav People's Army lasted only ten days; the EU-brokered Brioni Agreement led to Yugoslav withdrawal."
  ]
